Maendeleo Chap Chap, which is associated with Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua, will today meet all aspirants eyeing the party ticket.Interim secretary general Steve Kilonzo said the party is committed to offering transformative leadership and will field candidates countrywide."We will certainly be a force to reckon with in the general election. We expect more than 3,000 aspirants at the meeting,'' he said.Interim party officials will also be unveiled during the meeting at the Kenyatta International Convention Centre.Kilonzo, who spoke to reporters in Machakos town yesterday, said those interested in joining the party as members are welcome in the meeting."I want them to learn about the party consciousness and be part of this historical change in our country," he said.Kilonzo said sitting politicians who want to run on the party ticket are also invited.